    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d538fn1">Sent to the White House Map Room in Washington as
                        telegram No. <gloss target="#t_Black1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Black</hi>
                        </gloss> 14. Delivered to the British Embassy at Washington for transmission
                        to Churchill in Canada.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hyde Park</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-26">26 August
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From the President to <gloss target="#t_CW1">Colonel Warden</gloss>, Personal and
                    Secret.</p>
                <p>Number 346. Your number 414.<note n="2" xml:id="d538fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> Wednesday, the First, is all right in every way. If the Subaltern wants
                    to go to Oglethorpe<note n="3" xml:id="d538fn3">Churchii’s daughter Mary visited
                        the Women’s Army Corps at Oglethorpe, Georgia, August 31–September 2,
                        1943.</note> it would give her more time in Washington if she were to come
                    down a day or two ahead.</p>
                <p>I hope <gloss target="#t_LW1">Lady Warden</gloss>
                    <note n="4" xml:id="d538fn4">Mrs. Churchill.</note> is getting a real rest and
                    that you are too. Also I hope that you have gone to one of the lakes. Be sure to
                    have the big one weighed and verified by Mackenzie.<note n="5" xml:id="d538fn5"
                        >Prime Minister Mackenzie King.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
